commit.message:
install_server: fix late_command.sh to avoid race conditions

To avoid race conditions between the injection of /tmp/puppet_version
(by the reimage cookbook) and d-i installing and finally running
late_command.sh, apply these changes:
* Default to Puppet 7 - in case d-i finishes very quick
  and runs late_command.sh, before we have the change to
  inject /tmp/puppet_versions, default to Puppet 7.
* Increase the time to wait before giving up checking
  /tmp/puppet_version to ~300 seconds, rather than
  less than a minute. Not being able to inject /tmp/puppet_version
  should be very rare and worth to wait for.

Bug: T369654
Change-Id: I106af8575fa44dcc9aa00a3bcc661beaec69ecc9

commit.message:
feat: Remove Explore URLs and make the normal URLs public (#2632)

* add groupSlug to most routes

* fixed more routing issues

* fixed jank and incorrect routes

* remove public explore links

* remove unused groupSlug and explore routes

* nuked explore pages

* fixed public toolstore bug

* fixed various routes missing group slug

* restored public app header menu

* fix janky login redirect

* 404 recipe API call returns to login

* removed unused explore layout

* force redirect when using the wrong group slug

* fixed dead admin links

* removed unused middleware from earlier attempt

* 🧹

* improve cookbooks sidebar
fixed sidebar link not working
fixed sidebar link target
hide cookbooks header when there are none

* added group slug to user

* fix $auth typehints

* vastly simplified groupSlug logic

* allow logged-in users to view other groups

* fixed some edgecases that bypassed isOwnGroup

* fixed static home ref

* 🧹

* fixed redirect logic

* lint warning

* removed group slug from group and user pages
refactored all components to use route groupSlug or user group slug
moved some group pages to recipe pages

* fixed some bad types

* 🧹

* moved groupSlug routes under /g/groupSlug

* move /recipe/ to /r/

* fix backend url generation and metadata injection

* moved shopping lists to root/other route fixes

* changed shared from /recipes/ to /r/

* fixed 404 redirect not awaiting

* removed unused import

* fix doc links

* fix public recipe setting not affecting public API

* fixed backend tests

* fix nuxt-generate command

---------

Co-authored-by: Hayden <64056131+hay-kot@users.noreply.github.com>

repository.name: mealie
repository.description: Mealie is a self hosted recipe manager and meal planner with a RestAPI backend and a reactive frontend application built in Vue for a pleasant user experience for the whole family. Easily add recipes into your database by providing the url and mealie will automatically import the relevant data or add a family recipe with the UI editor

commit.message:
Publish Version 0.5.0 (#32)

* Removed old cookbook folder.

This folder has been moved to deploy.d

* Resolve typo in container storage deploy.

* Fixed another typo.

* Added odh demo deployment.

* Fixed typo in ocs deployment.;

* Bumped version number.

* Cleanup of cli and container handling.

* Bug fix to odh demo dpeloyment.

* Version bump

* Added version pinning to farosctl command.

* Made many changes to cluster configuration.

In preparation for upcomming changes, much of the config was
streamlined.

* Added bastion hosts interface list injection to cli.

* First pass at router role.

Added a router role that should configure the bastion node to act
as a layer 3 router with firewall. This required quite a bit of
change to the configuration and inventory bits. I expect this has
broken other scripts, but I will find those as I go.

* Added role to create dhcp server on the bastion node/router.

* Added dns server installation to the router node.

* Added ntp-server and router-hardening roles.

This should complete the router creation.
** fingers crossed **

* Updated the farosctl command to manage its own ssh key.

* Cleaned up the data directory initialization to make it more seamless.

* Cleaned up router firewall rules.

* Adjusted router config to use localhost as DNS server.

In order for the router/bastion node to complete the install, it
must use the local DNS server for resoution of the cluster nodes.

* Changed the order for configuring router components.

The LAN bridge must exist before the DHCP and DNS servers can
be created. This means the nodes primary DNS server will not
exist while it is waiting to be created. For this reason, I've
added a secondary DNS server.

* Updated docs for creating router.

* Fixed the shell command in farosctl cli.

* Added configuration option to control ingress network routing.

* The bootstrap script no longer needs to control SSH keys.

This is now handled by the farosctl command.

* Updated create machine command to use the bastion node router.

* Many changes to update the host record deployment to local router.

1) moved create network playbook to apply host-records
2) added necessary configuration params for host-records
3) removed unnecessary config params
4) added wait-for managment-interfaces

* Initial changes to get create cluster to work with internal router.

* Open tftp port.

* open firewall for machine configs.

* Cleaned up create command.

* Removing the concept of providers.

* Updated file structure to have all playbooks in playbook dir.

* Fixed port forwarding to work with direct routing.

* Fixed issue with the loadbalancer ports opening in the wrong zone.

* Don't wait for machine config server to come up.

This service is not garaunteed to be available from the bastion
node and is not specified in the install docs.

* Added option to specify NIC used for install.

* Put management IPs in cockpit rather than hostnames.

This is better when using the router to allow external access.

* Specifying a NIC didn't work....

It seems that all NICs that can DHCP still will. This is undesirable.
For the time being, the easiest way to deal with it is to black hole
any MAC address that I do not want to be active.

* Updated README with BIOS requirements.

* Deleted duplicate become record in handler.

* Fixed bugs in firewall config and dns server config.

* Version Bump

* cleanup of merge artifact.

commit.message:
Update all Nextcloud apps

Apps added for major version 21:

  shareimporter: Import CIFS shares into Nextcloud

Apps updated for major version 20 and 21:

  analytics (4.0.2 -> 4.0.3):

    * Fix file picker not working
    * Fix donut chart selection in wizard
    * Fix inability to set "can navigate" for other than the very first
      user in the list
    * Fix Datasource: Undefined array key "user_id"
    * Make dataload faster

  bbb (2.1.0 -> 2.2.0):

    * Add optional avatar cache
    * Add command to clear avatar cache
    * Use injection for random generator
    * Remove deprecated api calls
    * Enable app for unit tests

  calendar (3.0.4 -> 3.0.5):

    * Re-enable events being editable locally by attendees
    * Fix reminder time zone picker and formatting

  mail (1.11.5 -> 1.11.6):

    * Fix priority Inbox Sync
    * Fix new Messages not loaded
    * Fix full links in plain text mails
    * Remove bold font for selected envelope(s)
    * Fix BCC for email recipients query

  officeonline (1.1.1 -> 1.1.2):

    * Avoid opening PDF files
    * Update dependencies

  onlyoffice (7.2.1 -> 7.3.0):

    * Add support for docxf and oform formats
    * Allow to create blank docxf from creation menu
    * Allow to create docxf from docx from creation menu
    * Allow to create oform from docxf from document manager

  phonetrack (0.6.9 -> 0.7.0):

    * Fix style issues

  recognize (1.8.0 -> 1.10.0):

    Changes for version 1.10.0:

      * Landmarks: Add 'landmark' tag to all landmarks
      * Implement commands: cleanup-tags & reset-tags
      * Fix classifier_faces
      * Clarify debug message
      * classifier_landmarks: Don't run landmarks models on 'landscape'
                              images to weed out false positives
      * classifier_landmarks: Increase threshold to 0.9 to weed out
                              false positives

    Changes for version 1.9.0:

      * Allow setting amount of used cores
      * Speed up image classification models in pureJS mode by using
        WASM
      * InstallDeps: Automatically enable pureJS on ARM
      * Implement landmarks
      * Reduce Background job batch size in pureJS mode
      * imagenet: Try to improve recognition of historic architecture
      * imagenet: Don't ignore volcano

  riotchat (0.10.1 -> 0.10.2):

    * Update Element Web to version 1.9.9

  sociallogin (4.10.0 -> 4.11.0):

    Changes for version 4.11.0:

      * Use oauth_user_id for Seznam.cz login

    Changes for version 4.10.1:

      * Fix connecting account with several custom providers
      * Update dependencies

  storj (0.0.5 -> 0.0.6):

    * Improve initialisation
    * Add Nextcloud 23 compatibility

  timetracker (0.0.72 -> 0.0.73):

    * Fix spent hours in goals not displayed
    * Fix GROUP BY queries
    * Use a formatted time if timegroup is daily
    * Improve HTML indentation
    * Add support for Nextcloud 23

  vibeetoee (1.0.0 -> 1.2.1):

    Project neither has a changelog nor a SCM repository and I'm tired
    of diffing stuff on their behalf. So instead of a changelog here's
    my recommendation:

    Don't use this app, since the authors apparently want to ensure that
    their code changes are as intransparent as possible. This is
    especially shady for an app that supposedly implements an encryption
    technology.

Apps updated for all major versions:

  carnet (0.24.2 -> 0.24.4):

    * Fix runtime error in NextCloud 20.0.11
    * Put carnet in a frame to avoid conflicting CSS

  cas (0.2.5 -> 0.2.7):

    Changes for version 0.2.7:

      * Fix PostgreSQL compatibility by adding surrogate "id" column
      * Fix randomly generated name for expiry index

    Changes for version 0.2.6:

      * Add Nextcloud 23 compatibility

  cookbook (0.9.8 -> 0.9.9):

    * Update translations

  cpanelmailsync (0.1.5 -> 0.1.6):

    * Fix saving the API Token in the settings page

  files_mindmap (0.0.25 -> 0.0.26):

    * Add support for Nextcloud 23 and 24
    * Add note about losing data if file has changed while editing

  majordomo (1.0.1 -> 1.0.3):

    Changes for version 1.0.3:

      * Add simple configuration of IMAP options
      * Do not poll IMAP mailbox if servername is blank
      * Lock list action buttons on policy change until save

    Changes for version 1.0.2:

      * Add Nextcloud 23 compatibility
      * Add depenency on "imap" extension
      * Do not assume that mod_rewrite is installed

  ncdownloader (0.5.0 -> 0.5.2):

    Changes for version 0.5.2:

      * Make it possible to set your own output template in settings

    Changes for version 0.5.1:

      * Add support for Nextcloud 23

  ownpad (0.6.16 -> 0.6.17):

    * Add support for Nextcloud 23

  richdocumentscode (21.11.6 -> 21.11.103),
  richdocumentscode_arm64 (21.11.4 -> 21.11.103):

    Update Collabora Online Development Edition (CODE) to cp-21.11.1-3

  side_menu (2.1.0 -> 2.3.2):

    Changes for version 2.3.2:

      * Fix hidden menu

    Changes for version 2.3.1:

      * Fix app not working with default menu

    Changes for version 2.3.0:

      * Add an option to keep an app visible in both menus
      * Add custom categories
      * Add auto-reload when settings are saved

    Changes for version 2.2.0:

      * Update icons
      * Use Nextcloud colors by default
      * Fix categories order in large menu

  timemanager (0.2.6 -> 0.2.7):

    * Bump compatibility to Nextcloud 23
    * Update JS dependencies
    * Filter selects – Add missing color customisations for dark-mode
    * Reports – Improve completeness of reports at the beginning and end
      of an interval

  tvshownamer (0.1.0 -> 0.1.1):

    * Add support for Nextcloud 23
    * Allow to hide matching entries in file list
    * Fix file detection with the word series
    * Fix files with no episode identification
    * Add a few titles and alt tags

Apps updated for major version 21:

  appointments (1.11.10 -> 1.11.12):

    Changes for version 1.11.12:

      * Add an option option to add custom text to event/appointment
        DESCRIPTION property

    Changes for version 1.11.11:

      * Fix interval tree bug: lookup might report busy slot as free
                               under certain circumstances
      * Allow non admin users to debug/dump own raw calendar data

  cms_pico (1.0.16 -> 1.0.17):

    * Update translations
    * Drop support for Nextcloud 20
    * Add support for Nextcloud 24
    * Improve CI and test workflow
    * Update dependencies
    * Add prefixes for database table indices

  gestion (1.2.12 -> 2.0.0):

    * Update translations
    * Refactor front-end

  hidesidebars (1.1.0 -> 2.0.0):

    * Add config parameter for usage in an iframe

  spreed (11.3.4 -> 11.3.5):

    * Allow joining open conversations which are also shared as link
      with a password
    * Don't force a signaling mode when starting/ending the HPB trial
    * Add conversation token and message id to search results

  terms_of_service (1.7.1 -> 1.7.4):

    * Fix user_id column length
    * Add index for performance

  twofactor_webauthn (0.2.14 -> 0.2.15):

    * Update dependencies

Apps updated for major version 19 and 21:

  fileslibreofficeedit (1.0.2 -> 1.0.4):

    * Fix wrong version number in app info

Signed-off-by: aszlig <aszlig@nix.build>
